<h1>Images</h1>
<p>Images in BaseWeb are handles responsively be default. You're also provided a few class modifiers for commonly used image styles as well as image alignment classes.</p>

<pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;img src=&quot;...&quot;&gt;</code></pre>

<div class="demo">
  <img alt="Placeholder image" src="./img/example-01.jpg">
</div>

<section class="subsection subsection-classes has-inner-subsection">
<div class="inner-subsection">
  <h1>Image Classes</h1>
  <p class="text-lead">Alignment modifiers are classes for images that help position them within the context of a document. There are also a few stylistic modifiers for commonly used image effects.</p>
</div>
<ul class="docs-list">
  
  <li>
    <h2>img.align-left</h2>
    <p>Floats an image to the left and adds top, right and bottom margins so that text wraps around the image properly.</p>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;img class=&quot;align-left&quot; src=&quot;...&quot;&gt;</code></pre>
    <div class="demo">
      <img class="align-left" alt="Placeholder image" src="./img/example-02.jpg">
    </div>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <h2>img.align-center</h2>
    <p>Centers an image by making it block and giving it left and right margins of <code>auto</code>.</p>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;img class=&quot;align-center&quot; src=&quot;...&quot;&gt;</code></pre>
    <div class="demo">
      <img class="align-center" alt="Placeholder image" src="./img/example-02.jpg">
    </div>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <h2>img.align-right</h2>
    <p>Floats an image to the right and adds top, left and bottom margins so that text wraps around the image properly.</p>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;img class=&quot;align-right&quot; src=&quot;...&quot;&gt;</code></pre>
    <div class="demo">
      <img class="align-right" alt="Placeholder image" src="./img/example-02.jpg">
    </div>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <h2>img.rounded</h2>
    <p>Adds rounded border radius based on the default border-radius setting <code>$border-radius</code>.</p>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;img class=&quot;rounded&quot; src=&quot;...&quot;&gt;</code></pre>
    <div class="demo">
      <img class="align-center rounded" alt="Placeholder image" src="./img/example-03.jpg">
    </div>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <h2>img.circle</h2>
    <p>Makes a circle effect on an image by adding <code>50%</code> border radius.</p>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;img class=&quot;circle&quot; src=&quot;...&quot;&gt;</code></pre>
    <div class="demo">
      <img class="align-center circle" alt="Placeholder image" src="./img/example-03.jpg">
    </div>
  </li>
  
  <li>
    <h2>img.polaroid</h2>
    <p>Adds a polaroid effect to an image.</p>
    <pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;img class=&quot;polaroid&quot; src=&quot;...&quot;&gt;</code></pre>
    <div class="demo">
      <img class="align-center polaroid" alt="Placeholder image" src="./img/example-03.jpg">
    </div>
  </li>
  
</ul>
</section>
